fields.transit: Melbourne is an easy city to navigate with our 'grid' CBD surrounded by beautiful parks, gardens and promenades. From the apartment you could walk to any area of the CBD or just hop on a tram - it's free within the CBD and Docklands areas! The train station is just a short walk away at Melbourne Central. We supply the apartment with a few Myki cards (public transport top up cards) but it's guests responsibility to ensure they are topped up to use. Myki cards are needed to get out into the inner urban and outer suburban areas. Here is a list of attractions so you can check how far they are from the apartment; City Circle Tram Stop - 200m Melbourne Central (Shopping & Train Station)- 250m Emporium Shopping Centre - 250m Bourke Street Mall - 500m The Victorian State Library - 500m China Town - 600m Flagstaff Gardens- 400m The Queen Vic Market- 500m The Old Melbourne Goal- 800m The Yarra River- 1km The Aquarium- 1km Federation Square- 1.2km ACMI- 1.2km The Arts Centre- 1.4km Crown Casino &
fields.street: Central Business District, Melbourne, VIC 3000, Australia
fields.neighborhood_overview: There really is something to be said about this part of Melbourne it's vibrant, fun and full of charm. By day it's a popular cafe corner and when the night rolls around this area is alive with dining and classy entertainment spots. If you're looking to experience some of Melbourne's 'laneway culture' then this place cannot be beat! It's also only a short tram ride to Melbourne's major sports and entertainment precincts, the Arts precinct or the city's popular shopping areas.
fields.space: Everything you'd expect from a Melbourne city apartment and more! Sleeping up to 5 guests with a queen bed, two singles and a double sofa bed, this apartment can cater for many requirements (plus 2 porta cots if required at no extra charge). The apartment is equipped with unlimited wi-fi and the TV is fitted with Chromecast and a DVD & Blue Ray player. The kitchen has ample cooking facilities and a dishwasher, all towels and bedding are provided. Aside from being a contemporary, clean and spacious apartment the key feature is it's location. Set right amongst Melbourne's premier restaurants, bars and cafes this is an ideal place for the out of towner.
fields.access: Guests will have private access to all areas of the apartment. Please note that there is unfortunately no car space provided with the apartment. It is best to arrive by taxi, Sky bus or public transport if possible. At the moment there is some construction happening on Hardware St and there may be some days where car or pedestrian access is restricted.

fields.host_about: Hi all, we are Airbnb hosts Simone and Jarrod. We live in Melbourne's eastern suburbs with our three children and as a family we love travelling and going on adventures in our own city. Jarrod loves soccer and sports in general and is learning to speak french. I love anything arts and crafts and enjoy selling my creations whenever I get a chance. Jarrod & I have really enjoyed our Airbnb experience of sharing our place with holiday makers from around the world. We take great care in ensuring that our apartment is cleaned and presented to a high standard and our guests are happy & comfortable. Please send us a message any time if you would like to ask any questions or make a booking.
fields.interaction: Please feel free to contact us through mobile (calls or text) or via email at anytime. We will endevour to meet all of our guests for key exchange whenever possible. If we are unable to meet you personally we will leave the keys in a lock box to give you flexibility of arrival time. We understand that communication with guests is crucial in order to provide guests with a great travel experience, we try to answer all messages promptly and keep our phones on 24hrs a day for your convenience.
fields.name: THIS IS MELBOURNE Hardware St CBD
fields.summary: Enjoy Melbourne's 'Laneway Culture' in this newly renovated apartment nestled in the very best part of the city, 200m from Melbourne Central and among some of the city's finest restaurants/bars/cafés... It's perfect!
fields.house_rules: We are really proud of this property and take great care to ensure it's presented in the best possible manner. We do expect guests to treat it nicely, to use fittings and appliances properly. No additional guests without approval and the apartment is not to be used for parties. Please report any damage or breakages and leave the apartment clean and tidy on departure. The unlimited wi-fi is a great benefit to guests and we welcome you to make the most of it however we expect you to use it legally. Please be respectful of the neighbours and keep noise to a minimum at night time. Please note there is no smoking allowed in the apartment, thank you.
fields.notes: The cafe next door is one of the best & most popular breakfast/brunch cafes in Melbourne which can mean there can be people waiting outside the atrium entry in the mornings and early afternoons. The apartment is set back from the street so this does not affect privacy or security of guests. There are many amazing breakfast options at the nearby Cafes but if you want to eat at the apartment we provide milk, cereal, muesli, fruit, tea, coffee & hot chocolate. We also have oil, butter, spreads, sauces if you want to cook. We provide umbrellas, a hair dryer & some toys for kids, so if you want to pack lighter you can keep this in mind.

You will be in the heart of the CBD right opposite the Southern Cross Station, which is the main hub connecting to the Melbourne International and Domestic Airport, Interstate trains, Bus terminal, Tourism departure point and lots more! Want to explore the city? The location is pretty much close to everything! China town, Crown Casino, Etihad Stadium, Docklands shopping area, Direct Factory Outlet (DFO), tonnes of Cafes and restaurants and heaps more! Feel a bit Lazy to walk? Tram stop is right in front of the building and the best part is, it is FREE for those who are only travelling around the city! fields.space: The WHOLE apartment ALL TO YOURSELF directly across Southern Cross Station (Main train station and transport hub) making this efficiently designed, inner-city place ideal for weekenders, business travellers or holiday goers. My place is comfy and furnished with everyday use amenities, and the building has a pool, gym, sauna, BBQ area, visitor sitting lounge, and also a rock climbing wall! Roomy and comfy for 1 or 2, just nice for 3, accommodates a maximum of 4. Inside the apartment is modern, nice and comfy. It has a open plan living area including the lounge with a full kitchen, a sleeping loft, dinning area, laundry facilities and a functional shower room. I have a full size double bed in my apartment for the first 2 guests and a sofa bed which pulls out into another double size bed for 2 more guests (3rd and 4th guests), convenient for those who are travelling on a budget. Else the sofa bed can fit your kids nicely and they may love the novelty of sleeping on a pull out bed :-)
fields.access: Please email/sms/message me or you could also ask questions about anything and in cases of emergency or urgent issues, you can ask the building managers on the ground floor. You will be able to access the apartment naturally and also all the Resort Style facilities including the gym, swimming pool, sauna, BBQ and pool side area, business/social lounge and rock climbing wall with the swipe card. There are three restaurants on-site on the ground floor including an Asian (PHO24), Modern Australian (Higher Grounds) and Breakfast/Grill trendy cafe (Pretty Mama) which all scores very highly amongst Melburnians.
